Watson pleaded guilty last Thursday to a felony charge of unlawful sex with a minor at a San Diego court, according to North County Times.  She faces up to to three years in jail and being placed on the sex offender's register.

Detectives were tipped off about possible inappropriate sexual conduct between Watson and the boy on July 30. She was arrested on August 10.

Watson is believed to have dated the boy for several months before her arrest. She has been on unpaid leave from her teaching post since her arrest and it is expected that her contract will be terminated following a school district meeting on December 11.

The 34-year-old is out on $45,000 bail until she is sentenced on February 6.

